PROJECT OVERVIEW
Team Workspace App
A focused collaboration tool for small freelance and student teams

Prepared by: DevGroup PH
Type: Side Project / Portfolio
Target Users: Small freelance teams, college project groups
Developer: Solo (Juan D.)

1. Executive Summary
Most team collaboration tools are either too bloated (Notion, Jira) or too generic (Google Docs, group chats). Small teams — especially freelance groups and college project teams — need something in between: a focused, fast workspace with just the features they actually use.

The Team Workspace App is a lightweight, real-time collaboration platform built specifically for small teams of 2–6 people. It combines a task board, shared notes, group chat, and an activity feed into one clean interface — no unnecessary complexity, no subscription fees, and no learning curve.

The project serves two purposes: it solves a real problem the team faces right now while building a portfolio-worthy full-stack application that demonstrates proficiency in modern web development, real-time systems, and product thinking.

Core Value Proposition: One place for your team’s tasks, notes, and conversations — without the bloat. Built for small teams who just want to get things done.

2. Problem Statement
Small freelance teams and college project groups face a recurring set of coordination problems:
•	Scattered communication: Tasks get discussed in group chats and forgotten
•	Fragmented tools: Project notes live in separate Google Docs with no connection to tasks
•	No visibility: No single source of truth — who’s doing what, and by when?
•	Overengineered solutions: Tools like Notion or Jira are overkill and slow to set up
•	Context collapse: Group chats mix work updates with casual conversation

For a freelance group actively taking on client projects, these problems directly affect delivery quality, client trust, and team morale.

3. Information Architecture
The app is structured in three levels: Workspace → Project → Task.

Workspace Level
•	Dashboard — All projects overview, member activity, quick stats
•	Projects — List of all projects with status and phase
•	Chat — Workspace-wide general chat
•	Activity Feed — Everything happening across all projects
•	Members — Team roster and roles
•	Settings — Workspace name, invite link, manage members

Project Level (tabs when inside a project)
•	Board — Kanban view (default), 5-column workflow
•	Overview — Project phase, progress %, milestones, standup posts, client link
•	Notes — Project-specific wiki with pinned notes
•	Chat — Project-level conversation with @mentions
•	Activity — Full project history log

Task Level (side panel or modal)
•	Details — Title, description, status, assignee, due date, milestone tag
•	Blocker flag — Mark as blocked with a reason
•	Comments — Thread of comments per task
•	Attachments — File uploads via Supabase Storage

