6. Data Model
High-level schema. Full RLS policies to be written before any frontend work begins.

•	workspaces — id, name, invite_code, created_by
•	workspace_members — workspace_id, user_id, role
•	projects — id, workspace_id, name, status, phase, progress_pct
•	tasks — id, project_id, identifier, title, status, priority, assignee_id, due_date, is_blocked, blocked_reason, milestone_id
•	milestones — id, project_id, name, due_date
•	notes — id, project_id, title, content, updated_by, is_pinned
•	messages — id, workspace_id, project_id (nullable), user_id, content, created_at
•	standups — id, project_id, user_id, done, next, blockers, created_at
•	activity_log — id, workspace_id, project_id, actor_id, action, metadata, created_at
•	attachments — id, task_id, user_id, file_url, file_name, created_at

7. Real-Time Strategy
Supabase Realtime handles live updates for chat messages, task status changes, and activity feed entries. Clients subscribe to relevant channels on mount and update local state on incoming events — no polling required.

•	workspace:{id} channel — workspace-wide chat, member join events
•	project:{id} channel — task changes, project-level chat, standup posts
•	activity:{workspace_id} channel — activity feed updates

