Development approach: Build Phase 1 for the team’s own immediate use. Real usage will surface what actually matters before investing time in Phase 2 and 3 features. Ship early, use it daily, iterate from there.

9. Risks & Considerations
•	Chat scope creep: Keep Phase 1 chat simple — no read receipts, no presence indicators, no pagination until Phase 2
•	RLS misconfiguration: Row-level security policies must be written and tested before any frontend work. A misconfigured rule can expose one workspace’s data to another.
•	Supabase free tier limits: 500MB DB, 1GB storage, 50MB file uploads. Design with this in mind; migrate to paid when needed.
•	Solo dev pace: Scope is ambitious for one developer. Phase 1 must be kept tight — resist adding Phase 2 features early.
•	Mobile experience: Without mobile responsiveness, teammates on phones will have a poor experience. Prioritize PWA support in Phase 3 at the latest.
•	AI integration (future): Claude API integration is planned but deferred. Features like task suggester and AI digest are designed so they can be layered in later without restructuring the codebase.

10. Success Metrics
•	The team uses it daily for their own freelance work by end of Phase 1
•	At least one other team outside the original group signs up and uses it
•	The project is live, deployed, and linked on all team members’ portfolios
•	A client or potential employer asks about it after seeing the portfolio

